frameDefinitions: A Landmark (in combination with the image schema evoked by particular targets) serves to pick out the final location of a Trajector in a construed or actual motion event.

This frame concerns an Addict's physiological or psychological compulsive dependence on an Addictant, the substance or behavior to which the Addict is addicted. '' 'Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became hooked on that designer drug instantly.'
A Subset is profiled against the Group it belongs to.
A member or members of a Class have just been  mentioned or are present in the discourse setting and now a different instance  (or group of instances) of the same class is referred to.
An Entity began its existence in the context of a Origin, which can be a place,  culture, time period, text, etc.
A Current_country is identified as matching or not matching the instance of the Discourse_salient_country.
frameExamples: Flights <t>into</t> Denver are not permitted at this time.
Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became <t>hooked</t> on that designer drug instantly.
<t>Of</t> all scenes that evoke rural England, this is one of the loveliest.
My husband left me for <t>another</t> woman -- and now wants to get back together again!
The Christian <t>origin</t> of this quote is from Isaiah 22.
<t><fex name='cur'>Foreign</fex></t> sales account for only 20% of IBM's income .
listRoleDefinitions: The relatively locatable entity which serves as a basis for determining the location of the <fen>Trajector</fen> using the <fen>Profiled_region</fen>.
The location (located with respect to the <fen>Landmark</fen>) which is profiled by the particular image schema pertaining to the locative relation.
The entity which is construed to be in motion, whose location at the end of the construed motion event is in question.
The time at which the <fen>Trajector</fen> is located in the <fen>Profiled_region</fen>.
The <fen>Addict</fen> is physiologically or psychologically dependent on a substance or a behavior.
<fen>Addictant</fen> is the substance or behavior to which the <fen>Addict</fen> is dependent.
The <fen>Group</fen> of entities which includes the <fen>Subset</fen>.
The general category of entity which has been referred to.
The instance of the <fen>Class</fen> that is added to the <fen>Initial_set</fen> of entities in the <fen>Class</fen>.
The previously mentioned group of entities of the <fen>Class</fen>.
The item whose <fen>Origin</fen> is under discussion.
The place or culture where the <fen>Entity</fen> was produced.
The country or countries that the speaker is indicating in the current instance, which may match or be distinct from the <fen>Discourse_salient_country</fen>.

The country that has been featured in the discourse, or that the speaker/hearer identify with or are located in; it serves to identify the <fen>Current_country</fen> by specifying it as the same or different.  This role is incorporated in the targets of this frame.
listRoleExamples: My Husband left me for another <fex>man</fex>!
A further five incursions <fex>over and above those noted for 1995</fex> took place in the first three months of 1996.
AutoPartsPlace.com offers discount prices on millions of import auto parts, <fex><t>domestic</t></fex> car parts, and car accessories.
